**Built #628 — AI external-platform EDIT form fields** → **PR #631** (off `main`, independent, no merge per review policy).

**The bug:** The edit drawer rendered no fields for AI platforms because `category-provider-fields.tsx`'s switch had no `ai` case and `"ai"` wasn't in `CATEGORIES_WITH_PROVIDER_FIELDS` — so `default_model` could only be changed via a raw API POST.

**The fix (6 files, single-source per #427):**
- `api-config.ts` — `ai` case in `buildApiConfig` (emits only `api_key`/`default_model`/`account_id`/`base_url`, deliberately **no `provider` key** since AI keeps `provider_type` in `metadata`) + `inferAuthType`→`bearer`.
- `ai-provider-fields.tsx` (new) — shared AI render fields; provider Select **disabled on edit** (with "can't change after creation" hint), conditional `account_id`/`base_url`, `default_model` + the #621 `@cf/` warning.
- `category-provider-fields.tsx` — registered the `ai` case + `CATEGORIES_WITH_PROVIDER_FIELDS`.
- `edit-social-platform.tsx` — seeds the locked `provider_type` from `metadata`; update omits `metadata` so provider_type/role/is_default are preserved.
- `create-ai-platform-component.tsx` — now builds via the shared `buildApiConfig("ai", …)`.
- `api-config.unit.spec.ts` (new) — **10 unit tests green**.

**Verification:**
- **Playwright-verified live at :9000** — created a dev cloudflare AI platform via API, edited it: provider greyed/locked, `account_id` shown, model editable, `@cf/` warning toggled, Save persisted `default_model=@cf/zai-org/glm-4.7-flash` with **api_key + `metadata.provider_type` intact**. Dev platform deleted after.
- **Zero new tsc errors** (the 6 in `edit-social-platform.tsx` are pre-existing rhf type-identity errors, confirmed identical on `main`).

**Persisted:** memory file `project_628_ai_platform_edit_fields.md` + MEMORY.md pointer, CODEBASE_MAP recipe, 3 BEST_PRACTICES bullets (login race, shared testid, in-place tsc-diff trick). Handoff posted on #628 + #352 pointer updated + `write-handoff.sh` run.

