The final #569 UI render slice: an OpenPanel-style **Hourly / Daily** segmented toggle on the analytics modal's **Visitors** chart. New self-contained `analytics-visitors-timeseries-card.tsx` wired to the server `GET /admin/analytics-events/timeseries` endpoint via the existing `useAnalyticsTimeseries` hook. Replaced the old client-side `recent_events`-derived chart; only an import + mount edit lands in the central modal file (stacks cleanly).

### Two load-bearing bugs fixed (surfaced as the endpoint's first UI consumer)
1. `useAnalyticsTimeseries` returned `res.body` (= `undefined`; `sdk.client.fetch` resolves the parsed body directly) → react-query rejected. Now returns `res`.
2. The `get-analytics-timeseries` workflow returned **0 buckets** — JSON-serialized Date inputs made the fill-loop compare `Date <= string` → `NaN`, so it never ran. Normalized to `new Date()`. Verified live: 0 → 31 daily / 25 hourly buckets.

